59
00:03:47,610 --> 00:03:51,720
What metric you're testing against it could be like, I want to know if this interaction works.

60
00:03:51,720 --> 00:03:54,960
I want to know if the users actually are interested in my product.

61
00:03:54,990 --> 00:03:58,200
You learn from those results and then you build again.

62
00:03:58,320 --> 00:04:03,240
So wireframes really help you to kind of implement that build, measure, learn cycle.

63
00:04:03,240 --> 00:04:05,610
So I want you always to think about that.

64
00:04:05,610 --> 00:04:11,790
Whenever you're kind of testing with users or just talking to other clients or stakeholders, you keep

65
00:04:11,790 --> 00:04:16,260
that in the back of your mind because the design process isn't linear, it's very iterative.

66
00:04:16,589 --> 00:04:19,050
So how can we use them?

